  "text": "This task identifies all Java source files in apache/kafka that implement the GroupCoordinator, including the group metadata state machine and request handlers. The Apache Kafka group coordinator is responsible for managing consumer groups and coordinating rebalancing operations.\n\n## State Machines\n\nThe repository contains three main state machines for different group types:\n\n1. **ClassicGroupState** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/classic/ClassicGroupState.java): Defines the state machine for classic consumer groups with five states:\n   - EMPTY: Group has no members, lingers until offsets expire\n   - PREPARING_REBALANCE: Group is preparing to rebalance, heartbeats trigger REBALANCE_IN_PROGRESS errors\n   - COMPLETING_REBALANCE: Group awaits assignment from leader, sync group requests are parked\n   - STABLE: Group is stable, members send normal heartbeats\n   - DEAD: Final state before group metadata cleanup\n\n2. **ConsumerGroupState** (in sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/consumer/ConsumerGroup.java): States for the modern consumer group protocol:\n   - EMPTY, ASSIGNING, RECONCILING, STABLE, DEAD\n\n3. **ShareGroupState** and other modern group states in sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/share/\n\n## Core Components\n\n### GroupCoordinator Interface\n- **File**: group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinator.java\n- **Key Methods**:\n  - `joinGroup()`: Handles JoinGroup requests for classic groups\n  - `syncGroup()`: Handles SyncGroup requests for classic groups\n  - `heartbeat()`: Processes heartbeat requests from classic group members\n  - `consumerGroupHeartbeat()`: Modern consumer group heartbeat processing\n  - `leaveGroup()`: Handles member departure\n  - Additional methods for shares groups, streams groups, offset management\n\n### GroupCoordinatorService\n- **File**: group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorService.java\n- **Purpose**: Concrete implementation of the GroupCoordinator interface\n- **Key Methods**:\n  - `joinGroup()`: Delegates to GroupCoordinatorShard with write operation\n  - `syncGroup()`: Schedules sync group operations\n  - Full lifecycle management of group coordination\n\n### GroupCoordinatorShard\n- **File**: group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorShard.java\n- **Purpose**: Handles per-partition coordination logic\n- **Key Methods**:\n  - `onJoinGroup()`: Processes join requests, handles state transitions\n  - `onSyncGroup()`: Processes sync requests, manages member assignments\n  - Implements CoordinatorShard interface for record-based state management\n\n### GroupMetadataManager\n- **File**: group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupMetadataManager.java\n- **Purpose**: Core state machine implementation for group metadata\n- **Key Methods**:\n  - `classicGroupJoinToClassicGroup()`: Handles join logic, member joins, rebalance preparation\n  - `classicGroupSyncToClassicGroup()`: Handles sync logic, generates assignments, transitions to STABLE\n  - `rescheduleClassicGroupMemberHeartbeat()`: Reschedules heartbeat expiry timeout\n  - `expireClassicGroupMemberHeartbeat()`: Called when heartbeat timeout expires, removes member, triggers rebalance\n\n## Group Implementations\n\n### ClassicGroup\n- **File**: group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/classic/ClassicGroup.java\n- **Purpose**: Represents a classic consumer group\n- **Key Method**: `transitionTo()` - State machine transitions with validation\n- Maintains members via ClassicGroupMember instances\n- Manages generation IDs and leader election\n\n### ClassicGroupMember\n- **File**: group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/classic/ClassicGroupMember.java\n- **Purpose**: Represents individual member metadata\n- Tracks session timeout, heartbeat metadata, supported protocols\n- Maintains lastHeartbeatTime for expiry detection\n\n### ConsumerGroup\n- **File**: group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/consumer/ConsumerGroup.java\n- **Purpose**: Modern consumer group implementation\n- Uses ConsumerGroupState enum for state management\n- Extends ModernGroup base class\n\n### ShareGroup\n- **File**: group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/share/ShareGroup.java\n- **Purpose**: Share group coordination (Kafka Share API)\n- State management for shared subscriptions\n\n## Heartbeat Expiry Detection\n\nThe heartbeat expiry mechanism works as follows:\n\n1. **Member Heartbeat Scheduling**: When a member joins or sends a heartbeat, `rescheduleClassicGroupMemberHeartbeat()` schedules a timeout using the member's sessionTimeoutMs\n\n2. **Timeout Expiry**: When the timeout fires, `expireClassicGroupMemberHeartbeat()` is called with the group ID and member ID\n\n3. **Expiry Handling**: The expiry handler:\n   - Removes the member from the group\n   - May trigger transition to PREPARING_REBALANCE if the group was STABLE\n   - Or transitions to EMPTY if it was the last member\n\n4. **Configuration**: SessionTimeout values are defined in:\n   - GroupCoordinatorConfig: Contains CLASSIC_GROUP_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS settings\n   - CommonClientConfigs: CLIENT-side session timeout configurations\n\n## Configuration and Metrics\n\n- **GroupCoordinatorConfig** (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorConfig.java): Central configuration for all group timeouts and limits\n\n- **GroupCoordinatorMetrics** and **GroupCoordinatorMetricsShard**: Track group state counts and other metrics\n\n## Key Files Summary\n\nThe implementation spans 26 Java source files organized in these directories:\n- `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/`: Core coordinator interfaces and implementations\n- `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/classic/`: Classic group implementation\n- `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/`: Modern group implementations\n- `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/metrics/`: Metrics tracking\n- `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/`: State enum definitions shared with clients"
}
